cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on Mobile Social Networks (MSNs) and proposes a new measure called Social-Relation based Centrality (SoReC) to identify central users in MSNs. This involves analyzing social network information to quantify the influence of each user in the network. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and processing data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
